    "This description applies to auto-regressive LLMs specifically, which are trained to predict the next word.",
    "Some LLMs, such as BERT (Devlin et al., 2018), are \"bidirectional\" in that they can use information that comes before and after a \"masked\" word to predict the identity of the word (e.g., \"The [MASK] sat on the mat\").",
